JOHANNESBURG – Journalist Jacques Pauw launched his new book, The President's Keepers, at Exclusive Books in Brooklyn Mall, Pretoria on Thursday. The author launched his book at the Hyde Park mall in Johannesburg to a packed crowd on Wednesday. UPDATE: Security Agency lays charges against Jacques Pauw, spy agency employees That launch, however, had to be abandoned due to issues with electricity supply. On Thursday, the State Security Agency said it had brought charges against Pauw relating to the confidential information disclosed in his book, which the Hawks confirmed they were probing.  Speaking after his book launch in Pretoria, Pauw said he will not reveal his sources and was not deterred by the state agencies' actions.  eNCA